== Japanese ==
[[Image:Japanese Katakana U.png|thumb|right|Katakana character ウ]]
===Etymology===
Simplified in the [[w:Heian period|Heian period]] from the ''[[man'yōgana]]'' ([[万葉仮名]]) kanji [[宇]] (''u''), taken from the top part of the character.

===Stroke order===
[[Image:Japanese Katakana U Stroke.png]]

===Katakana character===
'''ウ''' (''u'')

# the [u] phoneme, typically in words of non-Japanese origins
#: The third character of the first column of the [[katakana]] [[syllabary]], it is analogous to [[う]] (''u'') in the [[hiragana]] syllabary. The previous katakana character is [[イ]] (''i'') and the next is [[エ]] (''e'').

